stylometry: In our group project we looked at how many drivers it would take to deliver the pizzas that were demanded on a given night. We ran an @risk simultion that varied the number of driver from one to five. Once the simulation was run it determined that we should have just one driver to cover the pizza delivers. In the end I dont think that our model was correct. Once we added the waiting cost, and the fact that the drivers could only deliver 3 pizzas in an hour that conflicted with the fact that the people in the shop could produce 5 pizzas in an hour. I think that is where our model got off track because we had pizzas being made for delivery that we had no way of deliveing, but it was cheaper to lose money on those 2 pizzas than higher another driver.
